### OpenSpec

Specification-driven development. Specs live in `openspec/specs/`, change proposals in `openspec/changes/`.

Read spec files directly -- no MCP server needed. Create new specs by writing markdown files to the appropriate directory.

Docs: https://openspec.dev/

### Context7

Documentation lookup via MCP. Provides up-to-date library docs in context.

Usage: Add "use context7" to prompts when current library documentation is needed.

Docs: https://context7.com/

### Serena

Language-aware code navigation via MCP. Provides semantic code understanding through LSP.

Key capabilities (available as MCP tools):
- `go_to_definition` -- jump to where a symbol is defined
- `find_references` -- find all usages of a symbol
- `search_symbols` -- search for symbols by name across the project
- `get_diagnostics` -- get LSP diagnostics (errors, warnings)

Config: `.serena/project.yml`
Docs: https://oraios.github.io/serena

## Permission Governance

This project manages Claude Code permissions intentionally, not by accumulation.

### Settings files

| File | Purpose | Version-controlled? |
|------|---------|---------------------|
| `.claude/settings.json` | Shared team permissions baseline | Yes |
| `.claude/settings.local.json` | Personal overrides (machine-specific paths, local tools) | No (gitignored) |

### Current baseline

- **Profile**: [solo / team / open-source]
- **Default mode**: [default / acceptEdits]
- **Allow rules**: [N] (consolidated wildcards, reviewed [DATE])
- **Deny rules**: [N] (blocks .env, credentials, SSH keys, destructive commands, filesystem escape)

### Rules

- **No secrets in settings.** Never put passwords, API keys, or tokens in permission rules. Use `.pgpass`, env vars set outside Claude, or secret managers.
- **Deny list is mandatory.** Every project must have an intentional deny list blocking sensitive files and destructive commands.
- **Periodic sprawl audit.** When allow rules exceed 50, consolidate with wildcards. Review the allow list when it grows by 20+ rules since last review.
- **Filesystem scope.** The agent must not read or write outside this project's directory tree. Deny rules enforce this boundary.
- **Local overrides stay local.** `.claude/settings.local.json` is gitignored. Personal tool paths and machine-specific rules go there, not in shared settings.

## Context Management

- Stay under 100k tokens. Run `/compact` frequently.
- **One task per session** -- complete it, commit, exit.
- Before exiting, commit work and update issue tracker with any new findings.
- On fresh start, read this file, then check git status and recent commits to orient.
